kernel-5.15-rt-xanmod1 x86_64
Only run build-all-kernel-pkgs.sh

This kernel unlock some serious performance improvements
install this before wine-tkg

"Huge page tables" is a nice performance boost, but can be a minor security risk.
I might change something about the configuration but this has been working good for me for a long time.
You are free to swap the configuration before you build, just avoid changing the file name.
This configuration is not too far from generic Slackware.

https://xanmod.org/

Run first time to avoid conflicts with pkgs:
removepkg kernel-source kernel-generic kernel-modules kernel-headers

To install:
upgradepkg --install-new --reinstall /tmp/output-x86_64-5.15.36-rt41-xanmod1/kernel*.txz

Initrd command:
/usr/share/mkinitrd/mkinitrd_command_generator.sh -k 5.15.36-rt41-xanmod1

You can swap out the configuration file but don't add localversion, it have not been tested with the script.
And avoid changing the file name of the configuration. If you want to upgrade the kernel yourself, the script
is really nice for this, just build with the ???-xanmod1.tar.gz you want and put it next to build-all-kernel-pkgs.sh and go.

You might want to blacklist: /etc/slackpkg/blacklist

kernel-source
kernel-headers

Disclaimer you can use kernel-modules without a pkg conflict.
But remember you should have the appropriate kernel-headers installed when compiling software drivers or wine that target specific kernel functionality

Don't forget you're mkinitrd command and lilo/elilo or whatever bootloader you're using!
It happens like once a year when we had too much to drink right?
I always keep the huge kernel pkg for this...

Note: The current proprietary NVIDIA, VirtualBox, VMware Workstation / Player and some other dkms modules builds do not officially support THIS RT kernel

IGNORE_PREEMPT_RT_PRESENCE=1

Don't do this just use nouveau, if you have nvidia dont game with this kernel, maybe it works for you anyway..
BTW gaming is nice with this kernel :)
